examples.en: He is buried in sacred ground.
The Egyptians mummied all sorts of sacred brutes.
We have a sacred duty to find out the truth.
They'll make jokes about anything. Nothing is sacred to those guys.
The burial site is sacred ground.
Few things were sacred to Henry, but local history was one of them.
She saw motherhood as woman's sacred calling.
Some teachers tend to enshrine their personal preferences as sacred rules of English grammar.
The land is sacred to these tribesmen.
I hold with those who say life is sacred.
The sacred site required another sanctification after it had been defiled by the invaders.
He was anointed with sacred oil.
The lady of the house performs the sacred ritual of lighting two candles.
